<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-05-29T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-05-29T15:00:00-05:00" n="695" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d695">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/823: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Commission to Negotiate
                                        Peace</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss></hi><note n="20" xml:id="d695fn20">Transmitted
                                    to the Minister in China May 31.</note></head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-05-29T21:00:00+01:00"><hi rend="italic">May 29,
                                            1919, 9 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[<hi rend="italic">Received
                                        May 29, 8.43 p.m.</hi>]</dateline></opener>
                            <p>2336. Your 2082 May 24, 3 p.m.<note n="21" xml:id="d695fn21">See
                                    footnote 19, <ref target="#pg_694">p. 694</ref>.</note>
                                President asks that Legation Peking acknowledge message from
                                American Chamber of Commerce of China and state that matter which it
                                presents will receive his most attentive consideration. Lansing.</p>
                            <closer><hi rend="smallcaps">American Mission</hi></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>